args:
When Seimei announces a martial arts
tournament to ring in the new year, Elisanne
and Luca eagerly sign up. Each has their own
reason for participating, and the first challenger
to stand in their way is none other than Ieyasu.
Shortly before {player_name} is attacked\nby the Mukuroshu, an underground Hinomotoan\norganization...
What's eating you, Luca?\nBack home for the first time in forever\nand you're already bored?

Nah, it's not that. I was out pranking the
elder earlier, but when I was bracing for
the usual thunderbolts and lightning,
I got...nothing. No yelling, no anger.
Just a gentle smile and a ＂you know\nI won't be around to scold you forever.＂\nHe made it sound like...like he was...
Ahhh. I suppose you wouldn't have heard.\nLuca, I'm afraid the elder's condition has\nbeen deteriorating quickly of late.
Seriously?! No way. I'm not ready for\nthis! There's gotta be something I can do!
I've gathered those flowers you asked for,\nMarci. What will you do with them?
I'm, um, gonna make a crown for the\nmatron! She's been real stressed lately.
She talks to herself at night about lines,\nhow the bottom one is too red. So, I'm\ngonna cheer her up with a nice crown!
The bottom line...in the red? You mean\nto say the orphanage is struggling?!
Following the Mukuroshu's attack, Seimei of the\nOx Wyrmclan and his attendants travel to the\nHalidom to bring the year's good fortune.
This year's blessing will take the form of\na martial arts tournament.
Wait, no party? Instead of tasty grub,\nwe get...people punching each other?

Heh heh. I hear where you're comin' from.
But get this: it was Amaterasu who came
up with the idea. So you KNOW it'd gotta
be super smart-like!
See, the way we USED to do it, there\nwere only so many folks ya could share\nHinomoto's culture with in one go.
But a tournament allows more participants\nto enter and enjoy the year-end festivities.\nIs that it?
Precisely. Plus, with us entering too,\nwe can give you all a taste of how\nHinomotoans fight.
There'll be food stands for the crowd with\nmochi and osechi dishes too, staffed by\nLord Seimei's shikigami.
Okay, NOW you're talkin' my language!\nNothing says New Year's like a mouthful of\nmochi and that little envelope full of cash!

Heh, glad to see Hinomoto's culture
catchin' on so good. And yep, we'll be
handin' out gifts too, so don't you worry
your little head about nothin'!
Well, MY ears're perked up. Gifts, ya say?
Yup! The lucky winner of the tournament\nwill walk away with...drumroll please...\nYura's reflecting mirror!

Oh, y'know, just one of Amaterasu's divine
tool thingies. It's s'posed to serve as some
kinda vessel that can anchor yer worldly
thoughts in time and place.
The mirror reflects the viewer's memories\nof those they cherish most.
It offers nothing to a warrior, save perhaps\nsome meager comfort in weary times. All\nit can do is preserve a sweet memory.
Oh, and there'll be a fat cash prize, too,\njust like one of them little envelopes y'all\nlike so much!
A cash prize, hm? Inspiration strikes...
Anywho, we'd be tickled to have y'all there\nrepresenting the Halidom. Whaddaya say?
Hah! I like your collective spunk.\nWhat's got a fire lit under you two?
Nothing of note. It is simply a\nsmall...personal ambition of sorts.
Ditto that. Sorry in advance, but I'm not\npulling any punches this time around—\nno matter who I'm fighting.
I should hope not. We will see who\nemerges the victor, fair and square.
All right, settle down.\nSave it for the tournament, kids.
Aha ha ha. It sounds as though we'll have\na few participants from the Halidom, then.

Faaantastic! All we gotta do now is get
this thing up and runnin'. The next few
days're gonna be busier than a horse
durin' hay season!
We'll be in touch with more information.\nPerhaps you can pass the time procuring\nsome New Year's kimonos.
The day of the Hinomoto\nFortune Fighters Tournament...
Mmmmm, this mochi's like a party in\nmy mouth! And the osechi's even better!
Dibs on the next bite! Ooh, and they're\nserving up mochi stew at the stand over\nthere! Hustle, people!

Honestly... Notte can feast till she's
squishy as a mochi, but you're competing
soon, Luca. Or is eating yourself into a
coma part of your strategy?
Pshaw, I'm fine. I'm just grazing.\nStill, can you believe this crowd?

Quite the impressive turnout. I spy visitors
from all across the continent. The New
Year is off to a prosperous start indeed—
for the food stand owners, at least.
A sweet prize and cash reward'll do that.\nIt was all my old merc buddies were talkin'\nabout. Gonna be a tough competition!
Good. Stuff like this is only fun when\nyou've got a pack of tough opponents\nto chew through. Let me at 'em already!
And I'll be your personal cheer-faerie!\nBy the way, are you sure YOU don't want\nto enter too, {player_name}?

I am. I entertained the thought, certainly,
but in the end, I decided to help with
security instead. But I'll be cheering my
friends on with all my might. Good luck!
Just leave it to your boy Luca!\nOop—looks like Seimei's taking\nthe stage over there.
I thank you all for gathering here today.\nI am the host of today's tournament:\nSeimei of Hinomoto's Twelve Wyrmclans.
May the martial feats on display\ntitillate as you savor our signature\nbrand of Eastern hospitality.

Next, I will explain the rules. Due to an
influx of entrants, we will be holding a
fiend-hunting qualifying round before
kicking off the tournament proper.

We'll loose fiends upon the mountain.
The two entrants from each block who
defeat the most will go on to the main
competition.

Those block representatives will then
square off in our first round. For the
matchups after that, please refer to
the tournament chart.
Join me in wishing all our fighters the\nvery best of luck! And with that, I hereby\nbring the opening ceremonies to a close.
Yeesh, I could feel the wind pressure off\nthat one! The crowd was already having a\nblast, but that's REALLY got 'em going nuts!

Were those pyroblossoms, or an onmyodo
technique? Didn't have Seimei pegged as
much of a showman, but he sure proved
me wrong.
Indeed. I believe our orders were roughly\nto ＂lay it on extra thick,＂ given that this\nis our first big event of its ilk.
It's been some time, friends of the\nHalidom. I'm pleased to see you all\nlooking well.
It IS you! I'm happy to see you too, Ieyasu.\nWhat brings you all the way to Southern\nGrastaea?
Seimei requested my assistance with the\ninaugural martial arts tournament. I could\nscarcely refuse him.
What's more, the prospect of battle\npiqued Marishiten's interest. I intend\nto participate as a combatant myself.
*whistle* First Yoshitsune and now Ieyasu?\nWhat's yer entry number?
Oh! I'm 57. That puts us in the same block.\nAssuming we both pass the qualifiers, my\nfirst opponent would be...
Me, it would seem. Let us both give our\nutmost, then.

Of course. This is a competition, after all.
I will give no quarter—even to you, Ieyasu.
Pray that our next meeting will be in the
ring.
